Looking at Node.js source: `url.resolve(source, relative)` calls `url.format(url.parse(source))` to normalize the source. So if source is already an object, it formats it first. The difference between having `query: {foo: 'bar'}` vs `search: '?foo=bar'` in `URL.format`:

